      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p>Your gaze alone serves as a challenge to combat.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Intimidate 15 ranks</p><hr /><p><strong>Benefit:</strong> You can spend a Resolve Point as a standard action to challenge an opponent that can see you into single combat. Attempt an @Check[type:intimidate] (DC = 10 + your opponent’s total Sense Motive skill bonus, or 15 + 1-1/2 × the opponent’s CR, whichever is higher). If you succeed, the opponent can’t directly attack or target creatures other than you until it makes an attack against you, forces you to attempt a saving throw, or damages you (whichever comes first). It can, however, include other creatures in areas of effect that include you as a target. Either you or the target can end this ability early, but the character who does so is shaken for 1d4 rounds. A creature can be affected by this feat only once per day. This is a sight-based and mind-affecting ability.</p>"
